From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: GE-Proton <git@localhost>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 15:25:00 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] winepulse: Reset stream timing state after an underflow.

The original long-running Riddle Joker failure was caused by a 32-bit
libpulse ABI mismatch.  Wine now undefines _TIME_BITS before including the
libpulse headers, so pa_timing_info has the layout expected by libpulse and
the near-INT64_MAX read/write gaps no longer need a destructive stream
recovery.

A newer log exposes an independent failure after an ordinary underflow.  The
Pulse stream never reports that playback restarted, but pa_started remains
set and the stream remains the period's timing source.  DirectSound continues
mixing and releasing normal buffers while Wine incorrectly treats the stopped
Pulse timeline as active, and playback does not recover.

An underflow means the stream is no longer playing.  Clear pa_started and its
timer baseline when the underflow callback runs.  This makes timing updates
use the existing write-index catch-up path until Pulse invokes the started
callback, at which point the timeline is established again from fresh Pulse
timing information.  Do not flush the stream or rewrite Wine's local-buffer
offsets; both operations can discard valid queued audio during an otherwise
recoverable underflow.

---
 dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c | 9 +++++++++
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+)

diff --git a/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c b/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c
index 22222222222..33333333333 100644
--- a/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c
+++ b/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c
@@ -847,6 +847,15 @@ static void pulse_underflow_callback(pa_stream *s, void *userdata)
     struct pulse_stream *stream = userdata;
     WARN("%p: Underflow\n", userdata);
     stream->just_underran = TRUE;
+    stream->pa_started = FALSE;
+    stream->timeline_start_period_time = 0;
+    stream->timeline_start_stream_time = 0;
+
+    if (stream->period && stream->period->timer_stream == stream)
+    {
+        stream->period->timer_stream = NULL;
+        stream->period->adjust = 0;
+    }
 }
 
 static void pulse_started_callback(pa_stream *s, void *userdata)
